    "chemicalDescription": [
      "This is a filtrate of the product obtained by the fermentation of the whole plants, Thymus vulgaris (thyme) and Lysimachia foenum-graecum; the fungus, Poria cocos; the rhizomes of Atractylodes japonica; the buds of Magnolia liliflora; the fruit of Vitex trifolia; and the leaves and stems of Bambusa vulgaris by the microorganism, Aspergillus. The accepted scientific name for Poria cocos is Wolfiporia cocos."
    ],
